Notes: All numbers based on IRS migration data, values of less than 10 are suppressed (more data and information is available at https://www.irs.gov/statistics/soi-tax-stats-migration-data).
These data will not exactly match data from the Alaska Department of Labor and Workforce Development's population estimates, and may differ significantly.
All numbers based on 2010 Census geography. Kusilvak Census Area is the former Wade Hampton Census Area.
*The 2014 to 2015 IRS migration data show unusually low migration in Alaska and nationwide. The data is out of order with other years and sources.
Sources: IRS Tax Statistics; Alaska Department of Labor and Workforce Development, Research and Analysis Section
